 🔴 First: What is DP? (No coding, no big words)       
DP = Dynamic Programming                                                              
 
👉 Dynamic Programming means  

Do not solve the same problem again and again. Save the answer and reuse it.
 
That’s it. 
This is the whole idea of DP. 

🧠 Real-Life Example (Very Simple)

Imagine this 👇
   
You ask your friend:

“What is 5 + 5?”
 
He answers: 10

After 1 minute, you again ask:

“What is 5 + 5?”

❌ Stupid way: He calculates again
✅ Smart way (DP): He remembers → 10

📌 Remembering the answer = DP

🔹 Why do we need DP? 

Because normal recursion is slow 🐌
It repeats the same work many times.

Let’s see.

🔹 Example: Fibonacci (Classic DP Example)

Fibonacci numbers:

0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8 ...


Rule:

fib(n) = fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)

❌ Normal Recursion (Problem)

To find fib(5):

fib(5)
 ├─ fib(4)
 │   ├─ fib(3)
 │   │   ├─ fib(2)
 │   │   └─ fib(1)
 │   └─ fib(2)
 └─ fib(3)   ← SAME WORK AGAIN 😡
     ├─ fib(2)
     └─ fib(1)


👉 fib(3) calculated twice
👉 fib(2) calculated many times

This is waste of time

✅ DP Solution (Smart Way)

When you calculate fib(3) once,
👉 store it somewhere
👉 next time, reuse it

This storing place is called DP array

🔹 DP in One Line (Remember this)

DP = Recursion + Memory

🔹 Two Ways to do DP (Don’t panic)
1️⃣ Memoization (Top-Down)

Use recursion

Store answers in array

Example idea (not important now):

If answer already exists → return it
Else → calculate and store

